description:
&lt;p&gt;West Kent Health GP Federation is seeking to employ an experienced and driven Finance Assistant to support the Head of Finance with the day to day aspects of the accounting and bookkeeping of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will preferably hold a professional accounting qualification and have proven financial experience in book-keeping, payroll and managing bank accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Kent Federation as an established employer and provider of clinical and corporate services. West Kent Health offers favorable terms and conditions and is part of the NHS Pensions scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties will include but are not limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day-to-day bookkeeping/data entry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounts Payable:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Processing of Practice and supplier invoices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Ensuring appropriate authorisation of all invoices and expenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Timely payment of approved invoices and expenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payroll duties, including liaising with HR and our external payroll provider&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance of bank accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provision of accurate financial information, as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with information to be sent to external parties, as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be mainly remote working.&lt;/p&gt;
